    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-29T14:52:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-27T08:07:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.51/658: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-08-29T15:52:00-04:00"
                            notBefore="1919-08-27T18:00:00+04:53">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received August 29, 1919, 3:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at] Omsk.</p>
                <p>“370, August 27, 6 p.m. Today <persName corresp="#p_ESC1">Eliot</persName>,<note
                        n="14" xml:id="d218fn14">Sir <persName corresp="#p_ESC1">Charles
                            Eliot</persName>, British High Commissioner in Siberia.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MDJACC1">Martel</persName>
                    <note n="15" xml:id="d218fn15">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MDJACC1">Damien J. A. C., Count de Martel</persName>,
                        French High Commissioner <hi rend="italic">ad interim</hi> in
                        Siberia.</note> and myself advised <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> immediately remove gold reserve amounting (only two?)
                    hundred million roubles to Vladivostok. All foreign military experts here agree
                    this should be done as precaution. <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> refused, stating he felt able to evacuate gold later if
                    necessary. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.[”]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
